step.action:
Display the error to the user with the following information and options:
ERROR: File not found Path: {resolved_path} Referenced by: step "{step_id}", input "{input_name}" Original reference: {original_path_expression}
Similar files found: 1. {similar_file_1} 2. {similar_file_2}
Options: [path] — Enter the correct file path [skip] — Skip this input (step may fail or produce incomplete results) [halt] — Stop the workflow entirely [run] — Run the prerequisite workflow to generate this file

Halt the workflow and present a detailed validation failure report:


  VALIDATION FAILURE — Retry Exhausted

  Source: {file_path_or_data_source}
  Validation Rule: {rule_name}
  Attempt: 2 of 2 (initial + 1 retry)

  Expected: {expected_description}
  Actual: {actual_description}

  Details:
    {detailed_error_message}
    {line_number_and_context_if_applicable}

  Raw error:
    {parser_error_message}

  Suggestions:
    - Validate the file manually: `cookie validate {file_path}`
    - Check for encoding issues (expected UTF-8).
    - Ensure the file was fully written (not truncated).
    - Compare against the schema: {schema_reference}

Halt the workflow and present the API failure report:


  API FAILURE — {retryable ? "Retries Exhausted" : "Non-Retryable Error"}

  Tool: {tool_name}
  API Endpoint: {endpoint_url}
  Step: {step_id}

  Error: {http_status_code} — {error_message}
  Error Body: {api_error_response_body}

  Attempt History:
    1. {timestamp} — {status_code} {error_summary} (initial)
    2. {timestamp} — {status_code} {error_summary} (retry after 1s)
    3. {timestamp} — {status_code} {error_summary} (retry after 4s)
    4. {timestamp} — {status_code} {error_summary} (retry after 16s)

  Suggestions:
    - For auth errors: check API key in _cookie/_config/credentials.yaml
    - For rate limits: wait a few minutes and retry manually
    - For quota errors: check your API plan and billing
    - For server errors: check {tool_name} status page
    - Run `cookie retry {workflow_id} --from-step {step_id}` to resume

Produce a comprehensive cost report showing:


  COST THRESHOLD EXCEEDED

  Threshold violated: {threshold_name}
  Threshold value: ${threshold_value}
  Actual/Estimated: ${actual_or_estimated_value}
  Overage: ${overage_amount} ({overage_percent}%)

  Current Session Cost Summary:
    Approved budget:    ${per_episode_limit}
    Spent so far:       ${cumulative_actual}
    This workflow est.:  ${current_workflow_estimate}
    Projected total:    ${projected_total}
    Over budget by:     ${over_budget_amount}

  Cost Breakdown (this workflow):
    {per_scene_breakdown}
    {per_tool_breakdown}

  Budget Utilization:
    [████████████████████░░░░] {utilization_percent}%

  Options:
    [increase]  — Increase budget to ${suggested_new_limit}
    [lower]     — Switch to a lower quality tier
    [modify]    — Modify the SSD to reduce scope
    [skip]      — Skip remaining expensive scenes
    [cancel]    — Cancel the workflow

Add a quality flag to the asset in the workflow context:


  {asset_id}
  quality_review_needed
  {check_name}
  {score}
  {threshold}
  {timestamp}
  {step_id}
  {file_path}
  warning


The flag is stored in:
`context.quality_flags[]`
